**Title:** Transition Specialist/Data Assistant  

**Unit:** RISE Transitional Services  

**Reports to:** Community Operations Supervisor  

**Status:** Full Time- Regular/Non-Exempt

**Salary:** $45,000 - 50,000

**Location:** Long Island City  

**Days/Hours/Schedule:** 35 hours per week (various shifts)

***The Organization:***The Fortune Societys mission is to support successful reentry from incarceration and promote alternatives to incarceration, thus strengthening the fabric of our communities. We do this by believing in the power of individuals to change; building lives through service programs shaped by the needs and experience of our participants; and changing minds through education and advocacy to promote the creation of a fair, humane, and truly rehabilitative correctional system.

***Position Summary:*** The Fortune Society is seeking to fill the position of **Transportation Specialist/Data Assistant**, under the supervision of the Community Operations Supervisor. The Transportation Specialist/Data Assistant will be responsible for working in the community and will have limited engagement in NYC and NYS facilities. The Transportation Specialist/Data Assistant will support with conducting pick-ups of participants and transporting them to Fortunes community office(s) and/or other Community-Based Organizations (CBOs) or programs. When the Transportation Specialist/Data Assistant is not conducting pick-ups, the person will provide administrative support to the team, including collecting and entering data into multiple databases.


***Essential Duties and Responsibilities:***

* Conduct participant transport/pick-ups from NYC DOC facilities or NYS DOCCS facilities (downstate region) to Fortunes community office(s) or other partner organizations or affiliates;
* Collect and enter data from transportation activities and conduct data entry for other program activities and support with the improvement of collecting, maintaining, and processing data;
* Build and maintain internal/external relationships.
* Transport participants to scheduled appointments and meetings;
* Assist staff members with picking up and dropping off documents to stakeholders or participants and their families;
* Establish and maintain rapport with clients during pick-ups and drop-offs, and, when appropriate, inform them about Fortunes services;
* Advocate for needed services, support with resources and internal or external referrals;
* Maintain adequate records, and log information into spreadsheet or data management system in a timely manner;
* Maintain and monitor confidentiality of participant files;
* Process and submit all reports and documents accurately and in a timely manner;
* Establish standards that will ensure appropriate boundaries and suitable behaviors;
* All other duties assigned.

***Qualifications:***


* High School Diploma/GED certification required;
* Documentation, analyzing, research, decision making, conflict resolution and people skills;
* Adequate computer skills; Working knowledge of Microsoft Office Suite, particularly Outlook, Word, and Excel;
* Experience in providing services to individuals involved in the criminal legal system;
* Ability to be flexible- Days/Hours subject to change in accordance with program needs;
* Must be highly motivated and have strong oral and written communication skills;
* Bi-lingual in English and Spanish a plus;
* Innovation and initiative are a must;
* Must be willing to work in a fast-paced environment with varying demands;
* Time management and organizations skills;
* Have a valid drivers license with a clean driving history;

***Travel Requirements:***


* Required to travel to city jails and Fortune Society offices.
* May be required to travel to offices for meetings and/or trainings.
* May be required to travel to other CBOs to meet with/or support clients or drop off their property.

***Physical Demands:***

* Ability to drive, walk and/or stand for an extended period of time.
* Ability to travel corridors and walk up and down stairs frequently, daily.
* Ability to lift packages up to 25lbs.

**To perform this job successfully, an individual must be able to perform each essential duty satisfactorily. The responsibilities and requirements listed are representative of the knowledge, skills, minimum education, training, licensing, experience, and/or ability required. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable intervals with disabilities to perform the essential functions of the job.**

***The Fortune Society is an Equal Opportunity Employer. All qualified applicants will be afforded equal employment opportunities without discrimination because of conviction history, race, religion/creed, color, national origin, sex, age, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity, military status.***
